    "62 was employed.",
    "This allowed us to compare its performance with popular Bayesian optimization methods for hyperparameter optimization in ML-MC problems.",
    "The ML-MC model, configured with 10 epochs and batch sizes of 16, was tuned using an Adam optimizer.",
    "The learning rate was set within the range of 2 -5 × 10 -3 (with a maximum of 2 and a minimum of 5), and weight decay varied from 0.1 to 0.001 for other hyper-parameters.",
    "The effectiveness of the proposed models was evaluated using various established criteria including precision (P), recall (R), accuracy (Acc), and weighted F1-score."
